label.value: Bile Duct Papillary Adenocarcinoma
Bladder Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of bladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Pathologic staging is based on the histologic review of the radical or partial cystectomy specimen.  Microscopic examination and confirmation of extent of disease are required.  Laterality does not affect the N classification.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of bladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Bladder Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with tumor invading the muscularis propria. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer pT2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with tumor invading the superficial muscularis propria (inner half).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer pT2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with tumor invading the deep muscularis propria (outer half).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with tumor invading any of the following: prostatic stroma, seminal vesicles, uterus, vagina, pelvic wall, abdominal wall. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with tumor invading prostatic stroma, uterus, vagina.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of bladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.  Note: regional lymph nodes include both primary and secondary drainage regions.  All other nodes above the aortic bifurcation are considered distant lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with single regional lymph node metastasis in the true pelvis (hypogastric, obturator, external iliac, or presacral lymph node). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with multiple regional lymph node metastases in the true pelvis (hypogastric, obturator, external iliac, or presacral lymph node metastasis).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: B Lymphoblastic Leukemia/Lymphoma

value.value: A neoplasm of lymphoblasts committed to the B-cell lineage, typically composed of small to medium-sized blast cells.  When the neoplasm involves predominantly the bone marrow and the peripheral blood, it is called B acute lymphoblastic leukemia.  When it involves nodal or extranodal sites, it is called B lymphoblastic lymphoma. (WHO, 2001)

label.value: Bladder Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with metastasis to the common iliac lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of bladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for bladder cancer. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of bladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Primary tumor assessment includes bimanual examination under anesthesia before and after endoscopic surgery (biopsy or transurethral resection) and histologic verification of the presence or absence of tumor when indicated.  Appropriate imaging techniques for extravesical extension of the primary tumor and lymph node evaluation should be incorporated into clinical staging. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of bladder cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Bladder Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Bladder Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Bladder cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Bladder Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: (T4b, N0, M0); (Any T, N1-3, M0); (Any T, Any N, M1).  T4b: Tumor invades pelvic wall, abdominal wall.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  N1: Single regional lymph node metastasis in the true pelvis (hypogastric, obturator, external iliac, or presacral lymph node).  N2: Multiple regional lymph node metastases in the true pelvis (hypogastric, obturator, external iliac, or presacral lymph node metastasis).  N3: Metastasis to the common iliac lymph nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis.  M1: Distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of urethral cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Urethral Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of urethral cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Urethral Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of urethral cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage II B Lymphoblastic Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage II: Involvement of two or more lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (II); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in association with regional lymph node involvement with or without involvement of other lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (IIE).

label.value: Urethral Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pTa TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with a finding of noninvasive papillary, polypoid, or verrucous carcinoma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with tumor invading subepithelial connective tissue. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with tumor invading any of the following: corpus spongiosum, prostate, periurethral muscle.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with tumor invading any of the following: corpus cavernosum, beyond prostatic capsule, anterior vagina, bladder neck.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with tumor invading other adjacent organs.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urothelial (Transitional Cell) Carcinoma of the Prostate Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of urothelial (transitional cell) carcinoma of the prostate, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Urothelial (Transitional Cell) Carcinoma of the Prostate pTis pu TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urothelial (transitional cell) carcinoma of the prostate with a finding of carcinoma in situ and involvement of the prostatic urethra. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Refractory Primary Cutaneous T-Cell Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma

value.value: A T-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma that arises from the skin and does not respond to treatment.

label.value: Urothelial (Transitional Cell) Carcinoma of the Prostate pTis pd TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urothelial (transitional cell) carcinoma of the prostate with a finding of carcinoma in situ and involvement of the prostatic ducts. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urothelial (Transitional Cell) Carcinoma of the Prostate pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urothelial (transitional cell) carcinoma of the prostate with tumor invading urethral subepithelial connective tissue. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urothelial (Transitional Cell) Carcinoma of the Prostate pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urothelial (transitional cell) carcinoma of the prostate with tumor invading any of the following: prostatic stroma, corpus spongiosum, periurethral muscle. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urothelial (Transitional Cell) Carcinoma of the Prostate pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urothelial (transitional cell) carcinoma of the prostate with tumor invading any of the following: corpus cavernosum, beyond prostatic capsule, bladder neck (extraprostatic extension). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urothelial (Transitional Cell) Carcinoma of the Prostate pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urothelial (transitional cell) carcinoma of the prostate with tumor invading other adjacent organs (invasion of the bladder). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of urethral cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Urethral Cancer pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with metastasis in a singe lymph node 2 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with metastasis in a singe lymph node more than 2 cm in greatest dimension or in multiple lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage II Bladder Urothelial Carcinoma AJCC v6 and v7

value.value: Stage II includes: (T2a, N0, M0); (T2b, N0, M0).  T2a: Tumor invades superficial muscle (inner half).  T2b: Tumor invades deep muscle (outer half).  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of urethral cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for urethral cancer. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Urethral Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of urethral cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Urethral Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of urethral cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Urethral Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Urethral cancer in which there is no evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
